#: ../../source/working_in_xsheet.rst:95
msgid ""
"As part of the scene you can load Toonz raster and vector animation "
"levels (TLV and PLI), Toonz palettes (TPL), full-color images or "
"sequences of full-color images (BMP, JPG, NOL, PIC, PICT, PCT, PNG, RGB, "
"SGI, TGA, TIF and TIFF), clips (AVI and MOV), Photoshop documents (PSD), "
"vector images including animation (SWF), vector images (SVG) and audio "
"files (AIFF and WAV). Images or clips with alpha channel information once"
" imported will retain their transparency information."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/working_in_xsheet.rst:97
msgid ""
"It is also possible to load TZU and TZP files created with Toonz version "
"4.x: in this case the files will be automatically converted and loaded in"
" the TLV format."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/working_in_xsheet.rst:99
msgid ""
"Photoshop files can be loaded taking into account the layers the document"
" is made of (see  :ref:`Loading Photoshop Documents "
"<loading_photoshop_documents>`  )."
msgstr ""

