#: ../../source/working_in_xsheet.rst:689
msgid "A preview icon of the first drawing or image exposed in the column."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/working_in_xsheet.rst:691
msgid ""
"The icons on the xsheet column headers can either be displayed at once "
"when the scene is opened, or on demand by clicking on the column header, "
"according to the Column Icons option available in Xsheet > Scene "
"Settings."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/working_in_xsheet.rst:693
msgid ""
"An area where the object and center to which the column is linked is "
"displayed, that by default is Pegbar 2, center B (see  :ref:`Linking "
"Objects <linking_objects>`  )."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/working_in_xsheet.rst:695
msgid ""
"The column on the far left displays the frame number, with the cursor "
"indicating the current frame. The cursor can be used to set the current "
"frame and allows you to activate the onion skin mode to better check the "
"animation (see  :ref:`Using Onion Skin <using_onion_skin>`  )."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/working_in_xsheet.rst:697
msgid ""
"When the animation is played back, the xsheet scrolls according to the "
"current frame cursor position in order to display the current frame. To "
"disable the scrolling deactivate the Xsheet Autopan during Playback "
"option available in the Preferences > Interface dialog."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/working_in_xsheet.rst:699
msgid ""
"At the top of the frame number column there are buttons for creating and "
"navigating memos that can be posted in the xsheet (see  :ref:`Using Memos"
