#: ../../source/working_in_xsheet.rst:918
msgid "Using the Smart Fill Handle"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/working_in_xsheet.rst:919
msgid "The Fill Handle allows you to edit cells directly from within the xsheet."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/working_in_xsheet.rst:921
msgid ""
"It is the small tab appearing at the bottom of the cell selection. By "
"dragging this handle you can repeat a cell or a group of cells, you can "
"add cells, or you can delete the last cells of a sequence. The behavior "
"of the handle is smart: this means that the way cells are repeated, "
"added, or deleted depends on the selection content."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/working_in_xsheet.rst:923
msgid ""
"Editing cells with the Fill Handle makes the cells placed below the "
"selection shift up or down."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/working_in_xsheet.rst:925
msgid "**To edit cell content with the Fill Handle:**"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/working_in_xsheet.rst:929
msgid ""
"If you want to repeat a cell content for some frames, select the cell and"
" drag the fill handle down."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/working_in_xsheet.rst:931
msgid ""
"If you want to lengthen a progressive sequence, select the cells where "
"the sequence is exposed, and drag the fill handle down: sequence will be "
"lengthen according to the progressive numbering. For example if the "
"sequence is 1, 3, 5, the added images will be 7, 9, 11, etc. This works "
"for any step the sequence may have."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/working_in_xsheet.rst:933
msgid ""
"If you want a random sequence to be repeated, select the sequence and "
"drag the fill handle down: the sequence will be lengthened according to "
"the sequence numbering. For example if the sequence is 3, 6, 4, 1, the "
"added images will be 3, 6, 4, 1, 3, 6, etc."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/working_in_xsheet.rst:935
msgid ""
"If you want a progressive sequence to be repeated, first copy the "
"sequence first drawing at the end of the sequence, then select all and "
"drag down the fill handle. For example if the sequence is 1, 2, 3, 4, "
"copy the drawing 1 at the end of the sequence (the result will be 1, 2, "
"3, 4, 1), and the added drawings will be 2, 3, 4, 1, 2, etc."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/working_in_xsheet.rst:937
msgid ""
"If you want to delete some cells, select a region so that the cells you "
"want to delete are in the last rows, and drag the fill handle up."
msgstr ""

