#: ../../source/working_in_xsheet.rst:970
msgid "Working Globally with Frames"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/working_in_xsheet.rst:971
msgid ""
"It is possible to insert or delete frames affecting the xsheet as a "
"whole, or a selection of xsheet columns."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/working_in_xsheet.rst:973
msgid ""
"Inserting or deleting frames can be useful if you want to change the "
"timing of the animation, for instance if you want to slow down or speed "
"up an animation."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/working_in_xsheet.rst:975
msgid ""
"When a frame is inserted, the current frame cells are duplicated, and all"
" the following cells are shifted down. If some animation keys are defined"
" for object transformations and FX parameters, they will be shifted down "
"as well to keep the animation consistency (see  :ref:`Animating Objects "
"<animating_objects>`  and  :ref:`Editing FX Settings "
"<editing_fx_settings>`  )."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/working_in_xsheet.rst:977
msgid ""
"When a frame is removed, the current frame cells are deleted, and the "
"following cells are shifted up. If some animation keys for object "
"transformations and FX parameters are defined in the removed frame, they "
"will be deleted and following keys will be shifted up (see  "
":ref:`Animating Objects <animating_objects>`  and  :ref:`Editing FX "
"Settings <editing_fx_settings>`  )."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/working_in_xsheet.rst:979
msgid "**To insert a frame:**"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/working_in_xsheet.rst:981
msgid "Select the frame before which you want to insert a new frame."
msgstr ""

