msgid "Select the scenes for which you want to collect assets."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/working_in_xsheet.rst:1586
msgid ""
"Right-click the selection and choose Collect Assets from the menu that "
"opens: all the scene files that were located in external folders are "
"copied into the default folders of the project, and the related paths "
"used in the scene files are updated."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/working_in_xsheet.rst:1591
msgid "Scene Backup Files"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/working_in_xsheet.rst:1592
msgid ""
"When scenes are saved, backup files of previous versions are "
"automatically stored in a folder named as the scene, that is located in "
"``+scenes\\backups``  of the current project."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/working_in_xsheet.rst:1594
msgid ""
"The four previous scene versions are retained, and they are named as the "
"scene with a progressive backup number: the highest the number, the more "
"recent the backup."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/working_in_xsheet.rst:1596
msgid ""
"For example if you have saved seven times the scene named my_scene, four "
"backup versions of the scene named ``my_scene_3`` , ``my_scene_4`` , "
"``my_scene_5``  and ``my_scene_6``  are available in the "
"``+scenes\\backups\\my_scene`` folder."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/working_in_xsheet.rst:1598
msgid ""
"If you want to recover a scene backup version of a scene, you have to "
"remove the backup number so to have the correct scene name, and move the "
"file into the +scenes folder."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/working_in_xsheet.rst:1600
msgid "**To recover a backup version of a scene:**"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/working_in_xsheet.rst:1602
msgid ""
"Retrieve in ``+scenes\\backups``  the folder named as the scene whose "
"backup you want to recover."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/working_in_xsheet.rst:1604
msgid ""
"In the folder, retrieve the TNZ file related to the latest backup you "
"want to recover, and rename it removing the backup number so to have the "
"correct scene name."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/working_in_xsheet.rst:1606
msgid ""
"Copy and paste it into the +scenes folder, to replace the version you "
"want to scratch."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/working_in_xsheet.rst:1611
msgid "Printing Xsheets"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/working_in_xsheet.rst:1612
msgid ""
"An xsheet can be saved as HTML file in order to view it on any computer "
"by using an Internet browser, and to print it on paper."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/working_in_xsheet.rst:1614
msgid ""
"The HTML file contains a header with general information, several tables,"
" whose length and width you can decide, representing the xsheet with "
"exposed levels and objects movements, and a list of the levels exposed in"
" the xsheet with the related location on disk."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/working_in_xsheet.rst:1616
msgid ""
"If any sub-xsheets are used in the scene, they are displayed after the "
"main xsheet where they are exposed."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/working_in_xsheet.rst:1618
msgid ""
"The information displayed in the header and the appearance of the HTML "
"table can be set by editing the following files located in the folder "
"``OpenToonz 1.x stuff\\profiles\\layouts\\settings`` :"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/working_in_xsheet.rst:1620
msgid ""
"``xsheet_html.xml``  contains the information used for the HTML xsheet "
"header, and the size for the tables used to represent the xsheet content."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/working_in_xsheet.rst:1622
msgid ""
"``xsheet.css``  is a Cascading Style Sheet file that is used to define "
"the colors, layout, and other aspects of the HTML xsheet file (see below "
")."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/working_in_xsheet.rst:1624
msgid ""
"When using the Print Xsheet command, a dialog with information about the "
"location and name of the generated HTML file is displayed; then the "
"generated HTML file is displayed in your default browser."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/working_in_xsheet.rst:1626
msgid ""
"The HTML file is saved in the same location of the TNZ file; the CSS file"
" used for its formatting is generated as well, by copying the one located"
" in the folder ``OpenToonz 1.x stuff\\profiles\\layouts\\settings`` . If "
"a CSS file is already available in the location where the HTML xsheet "
"file is saved, it will be used instead of generating a new one."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/working_in_xsheet.rst:1628
msgid ""
"If you want to move the HTML xsheet file, you should move the CSS file as"
" well, in order to preserve the HTML file appearance as defined by the "
"CSS file."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/working_in_xsheet.rst:1633
msgid "Editing the HTML Xsheet Header and Table Size"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/working_in_xsheet.rst:1634
msgid ""
"The HTML xsheet header and the size for the tables used to represent the "
"xsheet content can be defined by editing the`` xsheet_html.xml``  file "
"available in the folder ``OpenToonz 1.x "
"stuff\\profiles\\layouts\\settings`` . It can be edited with any text "
"editor software, e.g. Notepad or TextEdit."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/working_in_xsheet.rst:1636
msgid ""
"The whole text is included in the tag ``xsheet_html`` , that contains the"
" elements ``page``  and ``info`` , where the different users and roles "
"are defined. The basic structure of the file is the following:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/working_in_xsheet.rst:1644
msgid ""
"By editing the ``page row``  and ``page columns``  values you can set the"
" size of the table used for splitting the xsheet in sections. The size of"
" the table allows you to fit each xsheet section to the paper size you "
"want to use to print the xsheet on paper."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/working_in_xsheet.rst:1646
msgid ""
"The ``info``  lines allows you to set information to be displayed in the "
"header, for example the production name."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/working_in_xsheet.rst:1648
msgid "In the example file you can find the following lines:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/working_in_xsheet.rst:1656
msgid ""
"These lines can be edited, and new lines, with the same syntax, can be "
"appended, to provide all the information you want to appear in the header"
" of the HTML xsheet file."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/working_in_xsheet.rst:1658
msgid ""
"By default the header contains the Project and Scene names and the number"
" of frames the scene consists of; this information cannot be edited, as "
"they are retrieved automatically from the scene file."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/working_in_xsheet.rst:1660
msgid ""
"The ``xsheet_html.xml``  file has to be well-formed, and so it can not "
"contain an opening tag without its related closing tag, otherwise "
"OpenToonz will not run. If you decide to edit the ``xsheet_html.xml``  "
"file, make a backup copy first in case you need to revert the file to the"
" original version."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/working_in_xsheet.rst:1662
msgid "**To edit the xsheet_html.xml file:**"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/working_in_xsheet.rst:1664
msgid ""
"Open the ``xsheet_html.xml``  file available in the folder ``OpenToonz "
"1.x stuff\\profiles\\layouts\\settings`` with a text editor application "
"(e.g. Notepad or TextEdit)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/working_in_xsheet.rst:1666
msgid ""
"**To change the size of the table used for splitting the xsheet in "
"sections:**"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/working_in_xsheet.rst:1668
msgid ""
"Change the ``page row``  and ``page columns``  values in the "
"``xsheet_html.xml``  file."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/working_in_xsheet.rst:1670
msgid "**To edit the information displayed in the header:**"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/working_in_xsheet.rst:1672
msgid ""
"Edit the ``info``  lines available in the ``xsheet_html.xml``  file, and "
"append new ones if needed."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/working_in_xsheet.rst:1674
msgid "**To check if the xsheet_html.xml file is well-formed:**"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/working_in_xsheet.rst:1676
msgid ""
"Open it with an Internet browser and check if all the elements are "
"displayed in a nested list where they can be opened and closed to display"
" or hide the related contents."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/working_in_xsheet.rst:1681
msgid "Editing HTML Xsheet Appearance"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/working_in_xsheet.rst:1682
msgid ""
"The HTML xsheet appearance can be defined by editing thexsheet.css file "
"available in the folder ``OpenToonz 1.x "
"stuff\\profiles\\layouts\\settings`` ."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/working_in_xsheet.rst:1684
msgid ""
"The ``xsheet.css``  is a Cascading Style Sheet file that is used to "
"define the colors, layout, and other aspects of the HTML xsheet file. It "
"can be edited with any text editor software, e.g. Notepad or TextEdit."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/working_in_xsheet.rst:1686
msgid ""
"Editing the CSS file requires some skill in the CSS language, but some "
"changes like table ruling thickness, or cell colors, can be easily done "
"by expressing the thickness in pixels and colors as an RGB triplet in "
"hexadecimal format."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/working_in_xsheet.rst:1688
msgid "Elements defined in the CSS are the following:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/working_in_xsheet.rst:1690
msgid "``header``  refers to the table used as header in the HTML xsheet file."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/working_in_xsheet.rst:1692
msgid "``table``  refers to the table used for displaying the xsheet sections."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/working_in_xsheet.rst:1694
msgid "``TH``  refers to the header cells of the tables."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/working_in_xsheet.rst:1696
msgid ""
"``first_numeric``  refers to the first numerical column of the xsheet "
"tables."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/working_in_xsheet.rst:1698
msgid "``fxcell``  refers to the table cells belonging to special FX columns."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/working_in_xsheet.rst:1700
msgid ""
"``subxsheetcell``  refers to the table cells belonging to sub-xsheet "
"columns."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/working_in_xsheet.rst:1702
msgid "``TD``  refers to the generic table cells."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/working_in_xsheet.rst:1704
msgid "``TH.frame``  refers to the frame column"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/working_in_xsheet.rst:1706
msgid ""
"``TD.levelcell``  refers to the table cells belonging to standard level "
"columns."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/working_in_xsheet.rst:1708
msgid ""
"The CSS files have to be written according to a specific syntax. If you "
"decide to edit the ``xsheet.css``  file, make a backup copy first in case"
" you need to revert the file to the original version."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/working_in_xsheet.rst:1710
msgid "**To edit the xsheet.css file:**"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/working_in_xsheet.rst:1712
msgid ""
"Open the ``xsheet.css``  file available in the folder ``OpenToonz 1.x "
"stuff\\profiles\\layouts\\settings``  with a text editor application "
"(e.g. Notepad or TextEdit)."
msgstr ""

